        "id": 3222623,
        "name": "Paul Seah",
        "username": "Paul_Seah",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ec9cab/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-24T04:25:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A little tight, maybe in a bit of an awkward phase, but this was clearly quality, and very enjoyable. I liked the nose on this. Subtle, never shouting, but with really nice notes of loamy earth, tobacco leaf and warm spice, all floating around a core of plums, black cherries, and just that little shade dark chocolate. The palate was not quite as developed or complex as the nose at this point unfortunately, but it was still really pleasant. Here, fine-boned tannins and bright acidity wound its way around juicy, high-toned notes of black cherries and plums, these laced with bits of spice and a nice twist of tobacco leading into a fine finish. Not the richest 1998 right bank, and this was actually a bit tight at the moment, maybe in a slightly dumb phase. It was nevertheless a really elegant, polished Pomerol. I would love to try it 8-10 years down the road, when it should be absolutely lovely.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-04T07:27:52.091Z",
