        "created_at": "2021-08-25T13:35:24.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My last time tasted about three years ago it was the weakest of three in a flight. The other Trotanoy marginally over VCC neither of which I felt were really at peak, but still showing well, and lagging was the Conseillante with an overly prominent bell pepper notes. I enjoy a little herb in my wine, but this was for the outhouse Loire fanatics on this board.</p>",
