        "id": 3224743,
        "name": "Paul Seah",
        "username": "Paul_Seah",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ec9cab/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-27T07:36:48.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"172992\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>The ch\u00e2teau are not a huge fan of the 1998, which was produced in a period of absentee ownership. It\u2019s a nice wine, but they felt it should have been better given the vintage\u2014and in the context of 1998 Cheval Blanc, Figeac, Evangile, it\u2019s hard not to agree.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Agree. A solid enough wine - but not outstanding as you would expect from a great right bank vintage like 1998. It underperformed the other great houses.</p>",
